node.text:
Thanks for all the love on the master bathroom at my #LHIStGeorge reno that I showed you last week 🥰 I wanted to give a special shout out to Bill at @oldebricklighting today. I sent him an idea of a sconce I wanted for this bathroom and asked if he thought he could make it for me. He quickly and graciously said yes, and these sconces are the result of his skill and ingenuity! Aren’t they so pretty? The shade pivots so that you can block as much or as little of the light as you want. Thanks Bill - you did an amazing job! 👏🏻 👏🏻 👏🏻 
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Kathleen Field - Utah Designer in Sundance. May be an image of laundromat and indoor.

node.text:
Laundry conundrum: You don’t have the space for a dedicated laundry room (not even a basement to hide them in or a large bathroom to share space with). Lots of people will need access to the washer and dryer, so it has to be in a common space, so what do you do? You make it as pretty as possible so that you still smile every time you walk past it! That’s what we did with this hallway laundry space at my #lhisundance cabin. We framed the washer and dryer, put a countertop above them, and dressed the wall up with a pretty tile! Eventually there will be a floating oak shelf on the wall above them for (pretty 😉) storage of laundry necessities, but this hallway laundry setup is still looking pretty sweet as it is!🖤
Builder @jwhhomes

node.text:
Say hello to the newly renovated master bathroom at our #LHIStGeorge reno!👋 (And be sure to swipe to see the original space 😬) This bathroom got a major facelift from it’s dated and brown original self when we got rid of all that dark tile and brought in this clean and pretty marble look tile from @atlasconcordeus called Eon Carrara. We used a 12x24 tile on the floor, and a pretty mosaic herringbone from the same collection for the shower. I’m so happy that we got rid of that walled in shower AND the wall at the end of the right side vanity so that we now have a view of that beautiful shower! 🖤
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
This bathroom reno from our #midwaymodernfarmhouse will always be a favorite 🖤 We needed to add a family bathroom upstairs that could accommodate a bunk room of guests (not all at the same time, of course 😅😆). So we relocated the upstairs laundry to a small space off the rec room, and gutted the existing laundry to create this nice, large bathroom. We also stole several feet of space from the too large landing at the top of the stairs to ensure that we’d have enough room for a double vanity, large shower, and separate toilet room 🖤 Now bunk room guests large and small have a convenient and handsome bathroom nearby…problem solved!
Design @lindsay_hill_interiors and @pink_peppermint_design 
Architect @ajarchitects 
Cabinetry @dreamwoodsutah
